#Setup

TEXT(beginproblem());


Context("Numeric");		# or Complex

#---------------Tolerance------------------#
Context()->flags->set(
tolerance=>.03,
tolType=>'relative');  #relative or absolute

#-------------- Image Scaling---------------#
$imgScale =0.5;
$width = $imgScale*1177;
$height = $imgScale*881;


#---- Random variables for this problem --------#

$mu = random(0.15,0.25,0.01);
$F = random(0.8,1.5,0.1);
$theta = random(30,45,5);
$thetarad = $theta*pi/180;
$dcm = random(10,20,1);
$d = $dcm/100;
$m = random(0.2,0.3,0.01);
$rcm = random(6,7.5,0.5);
$r = $rcm/100;

#---- Formulas to compute answers --------------#
$phi = atan($d/$r);
$TAB = ($m*9.81+$F*cos($thetarad)-$mu*$F*sin($thetarad))/(sin($phi)-$mu*cos($phi));
$NC = $TAB*cos($phi) - $F*sin($thetarad);
$angaccel = ($mu*$NC*$r - $F*$r)/(0.5*$m*$r**2);

########################################################;
#PGML

BEGIN_PGML	

[@ image( "20-R-KIN-DK-23.png", width=>[$width], height=>[$height]) @]*

You were able to obtain a roll of toilet paper during quarantine and put it to good use. If the roll rests
against a wall where its coefficient of friction is [`\mu_k=`][`[$mu]`] and you apply a force of [`[$F]`] [`N`]
at an angle of [`\theta=`][`[$theta]^{\circ}`] tangent to the roll, determine the angular acceleration of the precious
toilet paper.  
Assume the roll can be treated as a uniform solid cylinder with a mass of [`[$m]`] [`kg`], a width of [`11.5`] [`cm`], and a radius
of [`r=`][`[$rcm]`] [`cm`]. Point B is a vertical distance [`d =`][`[$dcm]`] [`cm`] from point A.

[`\vec{\alpha} =`] [____]{"$angaccel"} [`rad/s^2`]  [`\boldsymbol{\hat{k}}`]

END_PGML

